{"key":"post-9927960","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9927960</id>\n<content>You bring the water to a boil with the stove on it's highest setting until steam is escaping from under the lid.&amp;nbsp; This will happen about ten minutes after the water begins to boil.&amp;nbsp; At this time, set your timer to 90 minutes and reduce the stove to the minimum setting that will keep the water boiling vigorously.&amp;nbsp; You'll just have to experiment to find the setting.&amp;nbsp; Add small amounts of hot water during the cycle if necessary to prevent the kettle running dry.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9927961</next>\n<prev>9927901</prev>\n<first>9927834</first>\n<last>9928119</last>\n<when>1236452855</when>\n<utime>03/07/09 09:07 PM</utime>\n</post>"}